  "texts": [
    "This variant improved over QLoRA by 2-3%, confirming that dynamic rank allocation itself contributes significantly to performance.In particular, CommonsenseQA and OpenBookQA benefitted from dynamic adaptation to layer importance, but GSM8K showed weaker improvement, as it relies more heavily on sequential token-level reasoning.",
    "The model also converged faster than static-rank baselines, reinforcing that dynamic reallocation improves learning efficiency even without reward guidance.",
    "However, the full DRaFT-Q with both dynamic ranks and reward weighting outperformed this variant in every case.",
    "Impact of Quantization PrecisionWe tested DRaFT-Q in different quantization settings to study the role of precision and memory tradeoffs.",
    "Fully 8-bit training improved accuracy slightly (by 0.3-0.5The best results were obtained using the 4/8-bit mixed precision mode: base model weights in 4-bit NF4, and LoRA adapters, gradients, and optimizer states in 8-bit."
